    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Positioning Measurement Failure Indication handling in F1AP\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP library was missing the implementation for `cp_positioning_measurement_failure_indication()` function which is required for handling positioning measurement failure indications in 5G NR gNB. When the gNB attempted to process a PositioningMeasurementFailureIndication message from the AMF, it would either fail to compile or exhibit undefined behavior due to the missing function.\n\nThe issue was traced to a missing source file `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c` that should contain the positioning-related message handling functions. This caused linking errors and runtime issues when positioning procedures were attempted.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/COMMON/f1ap_messages_types.h`: Added `f1ap_positioning_measurement_failure_indication_t` structure definition\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: Created new file with implementation of positioning measurement failure indication functions\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: Created new header file with function declarations\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/CMakeLists.txt`: Added new source file to build\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_includes.h`: Added include for positioning ASN.1 headers\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_lib_extern.h`: Added include for positioning header\n\n"
}